==Old English==

===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*unþio-'', from Indo-European ''*unt-''.  Germanic cognates include Old Saxon [[uðia|ūðia]], Old High German [[undea]], Old Norse [[unnr]], [[uðr]].  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[unda]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /y:θ/

===Noun===
'''ȳþ''' ''f'' (''pl'' '''ȳþa''')
# a [[wave]] of water

===Descendents===
Middle English [[ythe]]

